---
# Self-hosted Renovate runner for Forgejo. Runs on a schedule (and on demand),
# reads renovate.json, and opens dependency-update PRs against this repo.
#
# To enable it:
#   1. Create a RENOVATE_TOKEN — a Forgejo access token (Settings >
#      Applications) with scopes: read:user, write:repository, write:issue,
#      read:organization (+ read:package if Renovate should bump packages).
#      Renovate's init reads your user, issues, and org labels, so a
#      repository-only token fails with "Authentication failure".
#   2. Save it as a repository- or organization-level Actions secret named
#      RENOVATE_TOKEN (Settings > Actions > Secrets). Org-level covers every repo
#      in the org, so you set it once. NOTE: a personal user-level secret is NOT
#      injected into org-owned repos — use the repo or its owning org.
#   3. (Optional) add a read-only github.com PAT so Renovate can fetch
#      changelogs/versions for github-hosted deps (actions/*, astral-sh/*, etc.)
#      without hitting api.github.com's unauthenticated rate limit. Renovate
#      reads it from the GITHUB_COM_TOKEN env var, but Forgejo forbids secret
#      names starting with GITHUB_, so store the secret as GH_COM_TOKEN — the
#      mapping below renames it.
#   4. (Optional) adjust the schedule below; trigger manually from the Actions
#      tab via "Run workflow".
#
# RENOVATE_ENDPOINT is derived from the running instance, so this works on any
# self-hosted Forgejo — no hardcoded URL. The `forgejo` platform supersedes the
# deprecated `gitea` one; on an older renovate image, set RENOVATE_PLATFORM to
# `gitea` instead.
name: Renovate

on:
  schedule:
    - cron: "0 6 * * 1"
  workflow_dispatch: {}

jobs:
  renovate:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    container:
      image: renovate/renovate:latest
    steps:
      - name: Run Renovate
        env:
          RENOVATE_PLATFORM: forgejo
          RENOVATE_ENDPOINT: {% raw %}${{ github.server_url }}{% endraw %}/api/v1
          RENOVATE_TOKEN: {% raw %}${{ secrets.RENOVATE_TOKEN }}{% endraw %}
          RENOVATE_REPOSITORIES: {% raw %}${{ github.repository }}{% endraw %}
          RENOVATE_AUTODISCOVER: "false"
          # Optional read-only github.com PAT for changelog/version lookups of
          # github-hosted deps. Secret is GH_COM_TOKEN (Forgejo bans the GITHUB_
          # prefix); Renovate reads it as GITHUB_COM_TOKEN. Unset if absent.
          GITHUB_COM_TOKEN: {% raw %}${{ secrets.GH_COM_TOKEN }}{% endraw %}
          LOG_LEVEL: info
        run: renovate
